article.description: Rylan Wells threw for 187 yards and two scores and added 50 yards rushing to help Jacksonville run away from NAIA Edward Waters 41-7 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Jacksonville runs away from Edward Waters in second half
article.linkText: Jacksonville runs away from Edward Waters in second half
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Rylan Wells threw for 187 yards and two scores and added 50 yards rushing to help Jacksonville run away from NAIA Edward Waters 41-7 on Saturday night. Prince Gray had 113 yards receiving and two touchdown catches, including a 78-yard strike in the third quarter to put the game away. Ulysses Bryant added 90 yards and a score on the ground for the Dolphins (1-1) who racked up 445 yards of offense while holding the Tigers to just 283. Jacksonville's Austin Yeloushan had a fumble recovery return for a TD early in the second, but the Dolphins led by only six points, 13-7, at the half. They put the game away in the third however, outscoring Edward Waters 28-0. Daniel Wright had 49 yards rushing and scored the only touchdown for Edward Waters, a 7-yard run in the first quarter.
